ize=1> I am currently level 9 on Nimu and was wondering....<br><br>1) When do we recieve chain?<br>2) Currently have put all points into hammer and battlesong. Where can I find a good droped two-handed hammer for my level?<br>3) I mistakenly put 8 starting points into piety instead of charisma. How bad will this affect me?<br><br><br>Thats about it. Thank you in advance<br><br><br><br> <p>Seloria: Cleric of 41 seasons Daughters of Avalon Albion-Guenevere Elorin: Blademaiden of 44.5 seasons  Scaan Gorrym Hibernia-Percival Valk: Skald of 9 seasons Nimu-Midgard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufubbor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fubbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/1/02 6:53:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> chain at 20<br>you can get ok drops in nissie at that level<br>as for the 8 pie if it was me I would reroll It dont take long to get back to level 9<br>my pick would be <br>dwarf skald<br>10 str<br>10 con<br>5 quick<br>5 dex<br>your specs sound good just keep songs even with your level and put extra points in hammer as you get them leave parry alone tell you get 40+ <p>Icebane  50 Skald Lancelot,</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jenovagawaine>Jenova Gawaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/6/02 10:01:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> 10 con<br>10 Str<br>10 Charisma<br><br>So many reports have came out relating Cha to damage output of DDs.  Cant make a skald without Cha at the start.<br><br>Jenova<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ubristolltheskald.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bristolltheskald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/16/02 5:48:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> And Yet ANOTHER point of view...<br><br>I plan to be a self sufficient Skald that is capable of tanking with the best of em, soooooo.....<br><br>10 STR<br>10 DEX<br>10 CHA<br><br>And my spec @ 50 will be:<br><br>50 Axe<br>43 BS<br>2 Parry<br><br>As Parry SUCKS (Read: is USELESS) in RvR, and I get my speed song at 43, the Axe spec @ 50 will let me get more hits in on = con players and higher con mobs.  That is enuf to convince me that i don't need the lev 46 Damage ADD song when I could get that damage add all the time, and hit more often, by having my Axe spec @ 50.  Also, Tyr's Fury Doesn't hurt. =)  Keep in mind, tho, that I have Tireless II as part of my realm abilities to compensate for the extra END that i will use as an axe wielder.<br><br>Good Luck!<br><br>Bristoll<br>Lv. 45 Skald/Galahad<br>The Midgard Regime<br>&quot;Casters??? Yummy...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uharleybrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HarleyBrown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/19/02 9:01:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> I really have to question the logic in only going 43 in Battlesong.<br><br>For 1 more point you get the last Direct Damage, which in my opinion is one of the class defining skills of the Skald. <p>Bragge Tunecrusher (Skald) <BR>Gunreth Doublebarrel (Berserker) <BR>Yelrah Mingunr (Hunter) <BR>Knights of Ni on Kay<BR>-------------------------------<BR>Ever dance with the devil in the moonlight?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvoleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/19/02 10:14:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> I tend to agree, I think 49 44 3 is the best spec...  even though the last DD shout is an endurance hog and very power inefficient (ie, cost lots more for not a huge increase in dmg), it is still the best way to ensure you have as much 'up front' damage as possible.  this is very important with a skald as we have about zippo in terms of defense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ujaliawolfsdottir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalia Wolfsdottir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 11:00:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> What's more, you can find equipment to raise your weapon skill to 50 without training it to 50, so it just seems off to me. <p><img src="http://users.rcn.com/jmaclear/rilee_sig.gif" height=170 width=408 alt="Rilee MacLear"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvoleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 2:15:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> yes, but overspeccing weapon past 50 DOES help you do more damage....  right now with items and realm tanks I'm at 46+14 for 60 total weapon spec and it is YUMMY. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uclapperoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 3:11:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> Yes, overspeccing does more damage, but with diminishing returns on investment.  Speccing BS to 46 will give you the last group damage add which also boosts your damage (and also everyone else's in your group).<br><br>Boring as it may be, I'm going with the cookie-cutter skald:<br><br>At creation, I spent:<br><br>10 str<br>10 con<br>10 cha<br><br>...and I stand by that decision<br><br>and in about 3 levels when I hit 50 I will be:<br><br>46 BS<br>44 Weapon<br>change in Parry<br><br>Plenty of +weapon weapons out there to boost your base at least +5, and by 50th level if you haven't at least gotten to R2 in RvR you've been pleveling way too long.  That gives you a base 50 weapon spec right there.  You can go over that with additional realm ranks and the various other +weapon items if you so desire (like the Malm gloves that give +3 to all weapon types). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/urognir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rognir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 11:56:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Skald questions...</span><hr size=1> Although I am a month behind on this thread I am also a skald on nimue (level 13) and looking to make some friends.  If you are still out there, send me a tell... I would be happy to exchange info or pass down items if it ends up that I am higher level (doubtful at this point hehe). <p>--Rognir Ratatosk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/5/02 6:55:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Specs</span><hr size=1> I kinda like the 46 BS, 46 weapon, 10 parry template myself <br><br>If you aren't concerned with &quot;style&quot; or looks, forget swords, axes are okay, but hammers have a definite advantage in RvR.<br><br>The cookie cutter template, whatever your starting race : 10 con, 10 cha, 10 str -&gt; those 3 stats have the most noticable impact in both PvE and RvR, 3 stats at 10 means you are not &quot;wasting&quot; points (going 15 cha and rest 10 points in either or both con and str seems okay though). Dex is very useful in PvE (helps parry and block), but not in RvR, so you'll want to skip it at character creation. Qui has for now a dubious effect on damage (you swing faster but damages goes down, duh ... you'll still do a bit more damage, but it's not as good as it could be) and helps evade, but skalds have only evade I. Pie and other stats don't help at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/5/02 7:00:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Speccing</span><hr size=1> ----<br>your specs sound good just keep songs even with your level and put extra points in hammer as you get them leave parry alone tell you get 40+ <br>----<br>I used another strategy personnaly : try to list at which weapon and battlesong spec levels you'll reach a &quot;mileston&quot; for your character (next useful style, next damage add song ...). Then put all your points into BS until you reach a milestone. Then, put all your points into weapon until you reach a milestone ... It may helps getting interesting abilities a bit sooner. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=8.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=8.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.threadControl?topicID=8.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="teamskaldfrm1">General Discussion<option value="teamskaldfrm6">Bug Forum - General<option value="teamskaldfrm7">Wish List<option value="teamskaldfrm9">Equipment Discussions<option valu